body: There could be a few nodes that have dropped down to CPU because they haven't been supported in the CUDA EP. Any such indicators from the logs ?
no, the models loaded without warnings

It seems that some parts of the model are run in CPU (seems ScatterND does not have cuda fp16 implementation):

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30328909/92989105-69708c00-f486-11ea-93ac-803a736d1674.png)
another part is at the end of graph.

To get best performance, those operator shall have cuda implementations for fp16.

BTW, fp32 is usually faster than fp16 when input size is small. If you increase the batch size from 1 to 512, probably fp16 can be faster.
